#MinIO Definition & Usage

Official Documentation : https://docs.min.io/community/minio-object-store/operations/deployments/baremetal-deploy-minio-on-ubuntu-linux.html
Version : RELEASE.2025-07-23T15-54-02Z

MinIO is a self-hosted, high-performance object storage solution thatâ€™s compatible with AWS S3. You can use it for:

Local S3 storage to test or develop applications without needing AWS

Storing backups of databases, logs, or other files

Hosting static files like images, documents, or frontend assets

Serving as a storage backend for AI/ML workloads or data lakes

Managing large binary files in CI/CD pipelines

Running S3-compatible storage in private cloud environments
